Habakkuk 2-3 <t>For still <f>ⓔ</f>the vision awaits its appointed time; </t><t>it hastens to the end — it will not lie. </t><t>If it seems slow, <f>ⓕ</f>wait for it; </t><t><f>ⓖ</f>it will surely come; it will not delay. </t>
Habakkuk 2-4 <pb/><t>“Behold, his soul is puffed up; it is not upright within him, </t><t>but <f>ⓗ</f>the righteous shall live by his faith. <f>[1]</f> </t>
Habakkuk 2-5 <pb/><t>“Moreover, wine <f>[2]</f> is <f>ⓘ</f>a traitor, </t><t>an arrogant man who is never at rest. <f>[3]</f> </t><t>His greed is as wide as Sheol; </t><t>like death <f>ⓙ</f>he has never enough. </t><t><f>ⓚ</f>He gathers for himself all nations </t><t>and collects as his own all peoples.” </t>
